    public interface ComponentImplementedI
    The interface ComponentI serves as a common supertype for all component interfaces in the component model.

    Description

    Basically, components have required and offered interfaces. A component interface will be either an offered, a required or a two-way interface, as defined in the three direct children interfaces. Because components are callable remotely, using Java RMI, all of these interfaces have to extend the java.rmi.Remote interface. For the same reason, all methods will have to add the java.rmi.RemoteException in their throws clause, and their parameters will have to implement the java.io.SerializableCreated on : 2012-05-23
